info.name: COMPULIFE API
info.description:
![image](https://compulife.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/api.jpg) ## Getting Started The easiest way to start using the COMPULIFE API is by clicking the **Run in Postman** button above. [Postman](https://www.getpostman.com/) is a free tool which helps developers run and debug API requests, and is the source for this documentation. Every endpoint you see documented here is readily available by running our Postman collection. COMPULIFE API access requires a paid subscription. If you have already purchased access to our API, you can obtain your COMPULIFEAUTHORIZATIONID from your original API access email. If you are interested in subscribing to our API, please email us at [service@compulife.com](service@compulife.com) or call us at (888) 798-3488 or (888) 798-3488. In addition to this Postman documentation, a paid subscription to the COMPULIFE API will include a package of example files to get you started.

## Need help? COMPULIFE is available to answer your questions. Please email us at [service@compulife.com](service@compulife.com) or call us at (800) 798-3488 or (888) 798-3488.

## IP Address Limits We limit each subscriber using their IP address. Only one IP address can be accessed using your API subscription. If you need more than one IP address for API access, you will need additional subscription(s) per IP address(es).

## User Access Limits With each quote, the REMOTE_IP of the user is required to be passed. This value is passed so to avoid a single user from scraping your API access. This limit will ensure that a single user cannot scrape your API access and will stop the user from accessing your API for 24 hours.

# Authorization For requests that require authentication, simply send this value with your request. Your authorization ID will automatically return data for the United States or Canada based on your subscription. If you are doing business in both the US and Canada, please contact us for a second authorization ID. COMPULIFEAUTHORIZATIONID:
